<subSubSection id="97EA653FFFFD78056FB6FB9BFDBAF94B" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="DF4F36B4FFFD78056FB6FB9BFDF0FBF7" blockId="1.[151,607,1047,1072]" box="[151,607,1047,1072]" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">
<typeStatus id="004B8816FFFD78056FB6FB9BFF66FBE8" box="[151,201,1048,1072]" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFFD78056E07FB94FDF0FBF7" authority="Olliff, 1886" authorityName="Olliff" authorityYear="1886" box="[294,607,1047,1071]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Silvanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="congener">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFFD78056E07FB94FE4EFBF7" box="[294,481,1047,1071]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Silvanus congener</emphasis>
Olliff, 1886
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF4F36B4FFFD78056FB6FBDEFDBAF94B" blockId="1.[151,1437,1117,1683]" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFFD78056FB6FBDEFF79FBAF" bold="true" box="[151,214,1117,1143]" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Note.</emphasis>
Morphological characters of the inclusion under study convincingly place it among 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFFD78056BA7FBDEFB53FBAF" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1837" box="[1158,1276,1117,1143]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Silvanidae</taxonomicName>
(antenna with 11 antennomeres, not moniliform; open mesocoxal cavities; subparallel body form; pentamerous tarsi; head and pronotum without sublateral carinae or grooves) and namely within 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFFD78056CBDFB26FBBDFB67" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1837" box="[924,1042,1189,1215]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Silvaninae">Silvaninae</taxonomicName>
(antennae clubbed; antennal scape comparatively short, about as long as wide; frons laterally without longitudinal sulcus; frontoclypeal suture absent; scutellary striole absent; tarsomere 4 smallest). The specimen under consideration is assigned to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFFD78056A68FB6DFEADFAF3" authorityName="Halstead" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Austronausibius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFFD78056A68FB6DFEADFAF3" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Austronausibius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the combination of the following characters, which distinguish the specimen from other similar silvanine genera having six teeth or undulations on the pronotal lateral sides: (1) antenna with 11 antennomeres and a club composed of 3 antennomeres (gradually developed club of 4 antennomeres in 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFFD78056B47FADAFB79FAAB" authorityName="Redtenbacher" authorityYear="1858" box="[1126,1238,1369,1395]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Nausibius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFFD78056B47FADAFB79FAAB" box="[1126,1238,1369,1395]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Nausibius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; club of 2 antennomeres in 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFFD78056E01FAFEFDDEFA4F" authority="Halstead, 1980" authorityName="Halstead" authorityYear="1980" box="[288,625,1405,1431]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Afronausibius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFFD78056E01FAFEFE13FA4F" box="[288,444,1405,1431]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Afronausibius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BB614B45FFFD78056EE7FAFEFDDEFA4F" author="Halstead, D. G. H." box="[454,625,1405,1431]" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" pagination="271 - 374" refId="ref5109" refString="Halstead, D. G. H. (1980) A revision of the genus Oryzaephilus Ganglbauer, including descriptions of related genera (Coleoptera: Silvanidae). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 69, 271 - 374. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1980. tb 01126. x" type="journal article" year="1980">Halstead, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFFD78056D8FFAFDFC7DFA4F" authority="Halstead, 1980" authorityName="Halstead" authorityYear="1980" box="[686,978,1405,1432]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Acorimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFFD78056D8FFAFDFCB6FA40" box="[686,793,1406,1432]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Acorimus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BB614B45FFFD78056C02FAFEFC7DFA4F" author="Halstead, D. G. H." box="[803,978,1405,1431]" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" pagination="271 - 374" refId="ref5109" refString="Halstead, D. G. H. (1980) A revision of the genus Oryzaephilus Ganglbauer, including descriptions of related genera (Coleoptera: Silvanidae). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 69, 271 - 374. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1980. tb 01126. x" type="journal article" year="1980">Halstead, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
); (2) dorsal pubescence weakly curved, pronotal and elytral margins not widely explanate (in contrast to dorsal pubescence composed of strongly curved setae and pronotal and elytral margins explanate in 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFFD78056DF9FA45FCECFA38" authorityName="Halstead" authorityYear="1980" box="[728,835,1478,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Acorimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFFD78056DF9FA45FCECFA38" box="[728,835,1478,1504]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Acorimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFFD78056C5BFA46FBAAFA07" authorityName="Halstead" authorityYear="1980" box="[890,1029,1477,1503]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Afrocorimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFFD78056C5BFA46FBAAFA07" box="[890,1029,1477,1503]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Afrocorimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); (3) head without antennal grooves (head with antennal grooves ventrally in 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFFD78056D56FA6AFCBCF9DB" authorityName="Halstead" authorityYear="1980" box="[631,787,1513,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Afronausibius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFFD78056D56FA6AFCBCF9DB" box="[631,787,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Afronausibius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFFD78056C71FA6AFB0DF9DB" authority="Grouvelle, 1912" authorityName="Grouvelle" authorityYear="1912" box="[848,1186,1513,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Eunausibius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFFD78056C71FA6AFC75F9DB" box="[848,986,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Eunausibius</emphasis>
Grouvelle, 1912
</taxonomicName>
); (4) antennomere 10 about as wide as antennomere 9 (distinctly wider than antennomere 
<quantity id="18089B51FFFD78056CA7F98EFC1FF9FF" box="[902,944,1549,1575]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.286" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" unit="in" value="9.0">9 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFFD78056C97F98EFB5BF9FF" authority="Grouvelle, 1892" authorityName="Grouvelle" authorityYear="1892" box="[950,1268,1549,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Silvanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFFD78056C97F98EFB99F9FF" box="[950,1078,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Silvanopsis</emphasis>
Grouvelle, 1892
</taxonomicName>
); (5) tarsomere 3 simple (incrassate in 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFFD78056EB8F9B2FD81F993" authorityName="Ganglbauer" authorityYear="1899" box="[409,558,1585,1611]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Oryzaephilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFFD78056EB8F9B2FD81F993" box="[409,558,1585,1611]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Oryzaephilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFFD78056D44F9B2FD4AF993" authorityName="Grouvelle" authorityYear="1892" box="[613,741,1585,1611]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Silvanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFFD78056D44F9B2FD4AF993" box="[613,741,1585,1611]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Silvanopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); (6) pronotum without crescentic depression (with crescentic depression towards base in 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFFD78056EEFF9D6FD91F9B7" authorityName="Redtenbacher" authorityYear="1858" box="[462,574,1621,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Nausibius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFFD78056EEFF9D6FD91F9B7" box="[462,574,1621,1647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Nausibius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); (7) short temples present; and (8) inner interstriae of elytra flat (convex in 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFFD78056FB6F9FAFDA7F94B" authority="Halstead, 1980" authorityName="Halstead" authorityYear="1980" box="[151,520,1657,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Pseudonausibius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFFD78056FB6F9FAFEFAF94B" box="[151,341,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="138">Pseudonausibius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BB614B45FFFD78056E7DF9FAFDA7F94B" author="Halstead, D. G. H." box="[348,520,1657,1683]" pageId="1" pageNumber="138" pagination="271 - 374" refId="ref5109" refString="Halstead, D. G. H. (1980) A revision of the genus Oryzaephilus Ganglbauer, including descriptions of related genera (Coleoptera: Silvanidae). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 69, 271 - 374. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1980. tb 01126. x" type="journal article" year="1980">Halstead, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
